      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, it sounds like your tomato plants might be suffering from a case of \"gibberish\" — a common ailment among tomato plants, caused by a lack of nutrients, particularly nitrogen. It's like they're trying to communicate in a language only they understand, but the message is getting lost. To help your plants, you might consider adding some compost or a balanced fertilizer to their soil. This should help them get back on track and stop their leaves from turning into a pale, yellowish hue. Just remember, plants are like little green friends, and we need to make sure they're getting the right kind of \"goblin\" food to keep them happy and healthy!",
